com.camerontec.catalys.server.ha.collections.distributed

Class Replicator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.server.ha.collections.distributed.Replicator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IEventListener<GroupEvent>, IDistributedCollectionWriteAckListener, IReplicator

    public final class Replicator
extends Object
implements IReplicator, IEventListener<GroupEvent>
    Helper used by distributed collections to replicate write requests.

    The implementation of method replicate(com.camerontec.catalys.server.ha.collections.distributed.IReplicable) is as follows:
    • If the local cluster node is currently primary and if there is at least one cluster member to replicate to:
      • Multicasts the write request to other cluster nodes.
      • If an exception is thrown by the communication layer when attempting to multicast the message, calls IReplicable.onReplicationAborted() on the given IReplicable and then re-throws this exception.
      • Otherwise calls IReplicable.onReplicationStarted() on the given IReplicable.
      • Blocks until the expected quorum of write request acknowledgments is received, up to the replication timeout, and then calls either IReplicable.onReplicationAcknowledged() or IReplicable.onReplicationUnacknowledged().
    • Otherwise calls IReplicable.onReplicationAborted() on the given IReplicable and performs no further action.
    The quorum of write requests acknowledgments is a dynamic value computed as follows:
    • Wl, Wr and Wa being respectively:
      • the write quorum at local site parameter attached to the local cluster node's site in the configuration,
      • the write quorum at remote sites parameter attached to the local cluster node's site in the configuration,
      • the write quorum at all sites parameter attached to the local cluster node's site in the configuration,
    • wl, wr and wa being respectively:
      • the minimum of the number of remote nodes at the local site and Wl,
      • the minimum of the number of remote nodes at remote sites and Wr,
      • the minimum of the number of remote nodes at the all sites and Wa,
    • Then the resulting quorum, W is the sum of wl, wr and wa.
    An instance of this class is constructed using:
    • The channel to use for distributing write requests.
    • An IClusterDefinition describing the cluster's topology
    • An IDistributedGroupController providing access to the state of the cluster.
    • A replication timeout.
    This class is also an IDistributedCollectionWriteAckListener in order to be notified of acknowledgments of write requests by other cluster nodes.

    This class is thread-safe. Multiple thread can invoke replicate(com.camerontec.catalys.server.ha.collections.distributed.IReplicable) simultaneously. The only contention is on the value of W which only gets re-calculated when a change happens in the cluster state.

      • replicate

        public void replicate(IReplicable replicable)
        Description copied from interface: IReplicator
        Replicates a write request to other cluster nodes and blocks until the expected quorum of write acknowledgments has been received.

        Takes a single IReplicable argument that wraps the actual IByteArrayStore.WriteRequest to replicate. Calls back into the given IReplicable's IReplicable.onReplicationAcknowledged() method to indicate whether or not replication did happen (replication only happens if there are other nodes to replicate to). Then, in the case where replication did happen, blocks until the expected quorum of write acknowledgments has been received or a timeout is reached.
        Specified by:
        replicate in interface IReplicator
        Parameters:
        replicable - wrapper around the actual IByteArrayStore.WriteRequest to replicate
